Package: diffShrinkHDR
Title: High Dimensional Regression with Different Shrinkage
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Reza", "Drikvandi", email = "reza.drikvandi@durham.ac.uk", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9958-0422"))
Description: Implements the method proposed in Drikvandi (2025) for high dimensional regression 
    with separate shrinkage for parameters of interest and nuisance parameters. 
    Uses smooth penalties (L2) for parameters of interest to control estimation variance 
    and non-smooth penalties (L1) for nuisance parameters to induce sparsity. 
    Handles both cases where parameters of interest are specified a priori or 
    identified via correlation learning. 
    Provides debiased estimates, confidence intervals, and hypothesis tests.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0),
    glmnet,
    SIS,
    expm,
    MASS
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
